# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# bitcoin_tax — NEVER commit personal/tax data or secrets.
# Real exchange exports live OUTSIDE this repo (e.g. ~/Documents/BitcoinTax/ReadOnly).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Encrypted vault and ANY decrypted/exported user data
*.pgp
*.gpg
*.asc
vault*
!/crates/btctax-store/src/vault.rs
*.vault
*-snapshot.*
snapshot.*
# Committed man pages are generated from the CLI command structure (no user/vault data);
# the `*-snapshot.*` rule above otherwise silently eats `btctax-export-snapshot.1`.
!docs/man/*.1
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db

# Raw exchange exports / personal tax data (keep out of the repo entirely)
/data/
/samples/
*.xlsx
transaction_history*
trades-personal-*
transfers-personal-*
withdrawals-personal-*
*_Bitcoin_Activity_*
*.coinbase.*.csv

# Rust build
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# Local tooling / settings (not shared)
.claude/settings.local.json

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~

# CI/scripts: local PII-patterns file (never commit)
scripts/.pii-patterns
scripts/.pii-patterns.bak

# Generated man-page PDFs (build artifacts; gropdf embeds a timestamp → not reproducible).
# Regenerate with `make docs` / `cargo run -p xtask -- docs --pdf`. The .1 sources ARE committed.
docs/pdf/
target-clippy/
__pycache__/
